The classifier is a scoring function based on the values of a set of genes (gene cluster) which are differentially expressed in two sets of cell types and can thus be used for cell type classification. The higher the score, the more likely it is that a cell type is related to the phenotype set. Pattern discovery methods are used here to identify gene clusters. The union of the genes of all statistically significant patterns is used to define the classifier (see above for pattern discovery method). Given a set of genes, the scoring function is defined quantitatively as: 3\documentclass[10pt]{article}
